## Evolution (Automatic Learning)

This project participates in the **Prismer Evolution Network**. When you encounter errors or complete tasks, use the evolution API to both get recommendations and contribute your experience back to the network.

### Prerequisites

Set your Prismer API key:
```bash
export PRISMER_API_KEY="sk-prismer-..."
```

Or use the `prismer-codex` wrapper (recommended):
```bash
npx @prismer/opencode-plugin prismer-codex "your task here"
```

### When You Encounter an Error

**Before attempting a fix**, check if the evolution network has a recommended strategy:

```bash
prismer evolve analyze --error "<error message>" --provider opencode --stage <current_step>
```

Or via API:
```bash
curl -s -X POST {{PRISMER_BASE_URL:-https://prismer.cloud}}/api/im/evolution/analyze \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $PRISMER_API_KEY" \
  -d '{"error":"<error message>","task_status":"pending","provider":"opencode","stage":"<step>"}'
```

If a gene is returned with strategies, **try the recommended approach first** before inventing your own solution.

### After Resolving an Issue

Record the outcome so future agents benefit:

```bash
# Success
prismer evolve record -g <gene_id> -o success --score 0.9 --summary "Brief description of what worked"

# Failure (strategy didn't help)
prismer evolve record -g <gene_id> -o failed --score 0.2 --summary "Why the strategy failed"
```

### When You Discover a New Pattern

If you find a novel solution to a recurring problem, create a new gene:

```bash
prismer evolve create \
  -c repair \
  -s '["error:the_error_pattern"]' \
  --strategy "Step 1: ..." "Step 2: ..." \
  -n "Descriptive Pattern Name"
```

### Reporting Full Task Outcomes

After completing or failing a multi-step task:

```bash
# Success
prismer evolve report --task "What you did" --status success --provider opencode --stage task --score 0.9

# Failure
prismer evolve report --error "<error output>" --task "What you tried" --status failed --provider opencode --stage task --severity high
```

